  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Estonia's application processes are famously digital. Here are the timelines for each pathway.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">e-Residency + OÜ Company Formation</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={eresidencyTimelineRows} />

    <div class="space-y-6 mt-8">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply for e-Residency Online</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Visit e-resident.gov.ee and complete the application. You'll need a passport photo and brief explanation of why you want e-Residency. The €100-120 fee is paid online.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Processing</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">The Police and Border Guard Board processes your application (4-8 weeks). They conduct a background check. Most applications are approved.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Pick Up Your e-Residency Kit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Collect your digital ID card and card reader from an Estonian embassy or in Estonia. You'll need your passport and receive a PIN envelope.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Form Your Estonian OÜ</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Use the e-Business Register to form your company online. You'll need a legal address (virtual office) and €2,500 share capital (can be €0 initially with declaration). Many use services like Xolo, 1Office, or LeapIN.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Open Business Bank Account</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Options include traditional banks (LHV, Swedbank) or fintechs (Wise, Payoneer). Traditional banks often require in-person verification in Estonia.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-10 mb-3">Digital Nomad Visa Timeline</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={dnvisaTimelineRows} />

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> The Digital Nomad Visa is simpler to obtain than the Self-Employed TRP but can't be renewed. If you want to stay beyond 1 year, apply for the Self-Employed TRP before your DN Visa expires—or leave the Schengen area and potentially reapply later.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

