  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does e-Residency let me live in Estonia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. e-Residency is a digital identity for running a business—it gives you zero residence, travel, or work rights in Estonia or the EU. To physically live in Estonia, you need a separate visa or residence permit (Digital Nomad Visa or Self-Employed TRP).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I access Estonian public healthcare as a freelancer?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Not automatically. Haigekassa (public health insurance) requires you to be employed and paying social tax. Freelancers typically need private insurance. The workaround is forming an OÜ and paying yourself a salary, triggering social tax and Haigekassa eligibility—but this adds complexity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the difference between DN Visa and Self-Employed TRP?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The Digital Nomad Visa is for remote workers with foreign employers/clients (€3,504/month income, 1 year, non-renewable). The Self-Employed TRP is for entrepreneurs building a business in Estonia (business plan required, up to 5 years, renewable, path to permanent residence).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How much does it cost to form an Estonian OÜ company?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The state registration fee is €190. You'll also need a legal address (virtual office: €30-100/month) and accounting (€50-150/month). Share capital is €2,500 but can be deferred. Total first-year cost including e-Residency: approximately €800-1,500 plus ongoing monthly fees.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Estonia's 0% corporate tax real?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, but with a catch. Estonian OÜ companies pay 0% tax on retained earnings (profits kept in the company). When you distribute profits as dividends, you pay 20% (or 14% for regular distributions). This is great for reinvesting in growth, less advantageous if you need to extract money regularly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I extend the Digital Nomad Visa beyond 1 year?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The DN Visa is explicitly non-renewable for a maximum of 1 year. After that, you must apply for a different permit type (like Self-Employed TRP), leave Estonia, or spend time outside Schengen before potentially reapplying. Plan your long-term strategy early.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

