    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Estonia offers a genuinely unique proposition for freelancers: the world's most advanced digital infrastructure, a startup-friendly business environment, and the e-Residency program for running an EU company from anywhere. However, it's crucial to understand what each pathway actually provides.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      e-Residency is for business structure, not residence. If you want to physically live in Estonia, you'll need the Digital Nomad Visa (short-term, non-renewable) or Self-Employed TRP (long-term, renewable). And regardless of pathway, freelancers need private health insurance—Haigekassa isn't available unless you're employed and paying social tax.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      For tech-focused freelancers who value efficiency, digital services, and EU access, Estonia delivers. The winters are harsh (be honest with yourself about this), but the summers are beautiful, Helsinki is a ferry ride away, and Tallinn's startup community is welcoming to digital professionals.
